        ## Modelling / simulations

        A vital part of S-POP is the *S. oneidensis* oscillation-system within the microbial fuel cell. Due to complications stemming from COVID-19, we were not able to test the system on the bench. However, we showed success in modelling the system. After running models with generic kinetic values, a representative model was produced. These models evaluate different conditions and simulate applicable variations.  The [Model](https://2020.igem.org/Team:Stockholm/Model#SystemofDelayedDifferentialEquations) showed that an oscillation can be obtained and can therefore be used to distinguish and identify different pollutants depending on the period of the oscillations.

